<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id46e0edac-3a70-11f1-a967-d35dac11796a" identifier="/us/usc/t26/s6414"><num value="6414">§ 6414.</num><heading> Income tax withheld</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">In the case of an overpayment of tax imposed by chapter 24, or by chapter 3 or 4, refund or credit shall be made to the employer or to the withholding agent, as the case may be, only to the extent that the amount of such overpayment was not deducted and withheld by the employer or withholding agent.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id46e0edad-3a70-11f1-a967-d35dac11796a">(<ref href="/us/act/1954-08-16/ch736">Aug. 16, 1954, ch. 736</ref>, <ref href="/us/stat/68A/798">68A Stat. 798</ref>; <ref href="/us/pl/111/147/tV/s501/c/1">Pub. L. 111–147, title V, § 501(c)(1)</ref>, <date date="2010-03-18">Mar. 18, 2010</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/124/106">124 Stat. 106</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="id46e0edae-3a70-11f1-a967-d35dac11796a">
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="editorialNotes" id="id46e0edaf-3a70-11f1-a967-d35dac11796a"><heading class="centered"><b>Editorial Notes</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" topic="amendments" id="id46e0edb0-3a70-11f1-a967-d35dac11796a"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Amendments</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">2010—<ref href="/us/pl/111/147">Pub. L. 111–147</ref> inserted “or 4” after “chapter 3”.</p>
</note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="statutoryNotes" id="id46e0edb1-3a70-11f1-a967-d35dac11796a"><heading class="centered"><b>Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" topic="effectiveDateOfAmendment" id="id46e0edb2-3a70-11f1-a967-d35dac11796a"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Effective Date of 2010 Amendment</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">Amendment by <ref href="/us/pl/111/147">Pub. L. 111–147</ref> applicable to payments made after <date date="2012-12-31">Dec. 31, 2012</date>, with certain exceptions, see section 501(d)(1), (2) of <ref href="/us/pl/111/147">Pub. L. 111–147</ref>, set out as a note under <ref href="/us/usc/t26/s1471">section 1471 of this title</ref>.</p>
</note>
</notes>
